{{infobox ethnic group| |group= Cheetah |poptime = |popplace = India |langs = • [[Hindi language|Hindi]] • [[Marwari language|Marwari]] |rels= • '''[[Hindu]]''' 40% |related= • [[Merat]] • [[Meo]] • [[Qaimkhani]] • [[Sindhi-Sipahi]] • [[Khanzada]] • [[Meena]] }}
The '''Cheetah''' or '''Cheeta''' are a community found in the state of [[Rajasthan]] in India. They are also known as Cheeta Thakur.<ref name="people">''People of India: Rajasthan'' Volume XXXVIII Part One, edited by B. K. Lavania, D. K. Samanta, S. K. Mandal & N. N. Vyas, pages 217 to 220. Popular Prakashan</ref> "Cheetah" or "Cheeta" are the gotra or linage of [[Meena]] community of rajasthan. their maximum population is living nearby areas of kota district like ramgangj mandi etc. == Present circumstances == The Cheetah are an endogamous community and observe village exogamy. The divide their territory into four zones, and marriage cannot occur within the zone. They live in close proximity with the [[Merat]] community, a Hindu Rajput group, with whom they share many customs and traditions. The Cheetah are agriculturist by occupation, with the majority being small and medium-sized farmers, with a small number being sharecroppers.<ref name=people />
