{{Infobox MP | name = Usman Badini | honorific-suffix = | office =Member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] | term_start = 1 August 2017 | term_end = 31 May 2018 |constituency= [[Constituency NA-260|NA-260 (Quetta-cum-Chagai-cum-Nushki-cum-Mastung)]] |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] |relatives = [[Mir Muhammad Yousaf Badini]] (brother) }}
'''Mir Muhammad Usman Badini''' ({{Lang-ur|{{Nastaliq| میر محمد عثمان بادینی}}}}) is a Pakistani politician who had been a member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] from August 2017 to May 2018.
==Political career== He ran for the seat of [[Senate of Pakistan]] as an independent candidate in [[Pakistani Senate election, 2009]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Senate polls today: 69 in the run for 19 seats|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/955620|accessdate=15 July 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=4 March 2009|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912161944/https://www.dawn.com/news/955620|archivedate=12 September 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=87 to contest 20 Senate seats|url=http://nation.com.pk/politics/23-Feb-2009/87-to-contest-20-Senate-seats|accessdate=15 July 2017|work=The Nation|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106005521/http://nation.com.pk/politics/23-Feb-2009/87-to-contest-20-Senate-seats|archivedate=6 January 2017|df=}}</ref> but was unsuccessful.<ref name="dawn/16july2017" />
He re-ran for the seat of Senate of Pakistan as an independent candidate in [[Pakistani Senate election, 2012]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Rind sees conspiracy against Bhootani|url=http://nation.com.pk/national/23-Dec-2012/rind-sees-conspiracy-against-bhootani|accessdate=15 July 2017|work=The Nation|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912161944/http://nation.com.pk/national/23-Dec-2012/rind-sees-conspiracy-against-bhootani|archivedate=12 September 2017|df=}}</ref> but was unsuccessful.<ref name="dawn/16july2017" />
He was elected to the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] (JUI-F) from [[Constituency NA-260|Constituency NA-260 (Quetta-cum-Chagai-cum-Nushki-cum-Mastung)]] in by-polls held in July 2017. He received 43,191 votes and defeated Mir Bahadur Khan, a candidate of the [[Balochistan National Party (Mengal)|Balochistan National Party]] (BNP).<ref>{{cite news|title=JUI-F’s Haji Muhammad Usman Badini wins by-polls in NA-260|url=https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/headline/jui-fs-haji-muhammad-usman-badini-ahead-in-na-260-by-polls/|accessdate=16 July 2017|work=Daily Pakistan Global|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715170442/https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/headline/jui-fs-haji-muhammad-usman-badini-ahead-in-na-260-by-polls/|archivedate=15 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref name="dawn/16july2017">{{cite news|last1=Shah|first1=Syed Ali|title=JUI-F wins NA-260 seat after tough contest with BNP-Mengal|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1345688/jui-f-wins-na-260-seat-after-tough-contest-with-bnp-mengal|accessdate=16 July 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=16 July 2017|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716135341/https://www.dawn.com/news/1345688/jui-f-wins-na-260-seat-after-tough-contest-with-bnp-mengal|archivedate=16 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chaudhry|first1=Fahad|title=PTI to contest NA 260 election result with 'undeniable evidence of election rigging'|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1345905/pti-to-contest-na-260-election-result-with-undeniable-evidence-of-election-rigging|accessdate=13 February 2018|work=DAWN.COM|date=17 July 2017}}</ref>
